  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently, we rely on React Native's NetInfo API to check whether there is internet connectivity. On desktop, for instance, this presents a problem as by default react-native-desktop's NetInfo module uses `google.com` in order to check network connectivity.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nAlthough it is now possible to invoke `setConnectionCheckUrl()` on Desktop in order to set a custom URL, it would be better to instead rely on active peers count as a definition of being online.",
